<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.175401>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Distribution of Rhynchocalamus barani n. sp. (star), R. m. melanocephalus (circle), R. m. satunini (triangle) and R. arabicus (square) [R. barani n. sp. — Amanos Mountain, Hatay­Turkey. R. m. melanocephalus — 1. Kairo­ Egypt, 2. Sinai­Halbinsel, 20 km NE of St. Katherinen­Klosters­Egypt, 3. Perta­Jordan, 4. Karak (= Kerak) ­ Jordan, 5. Kidron Valley­Jerusalem­Israel, 6. approx. registered (after Gasperetti 1988), 7. Jerusalem­Israel, 8. Tel Aviv (= Jaffa) ­ Israel, 9. Haifa­Israel, 10. Tiberias­Israel, 11. Amman­Jordan, 12. Azraq­Jordan, 13. Golan­Syria, 14. approx. registered­ Lebanon, 15. Mezze­Damaskus­Syria, 16. Beirut­Lebanon, 17. Bcharré­Lebanon, 18. Latakia (= Ladakia) ­ Syria, 19. 20 km S of Harbiye. R. m. satunini — 1. Adana­Turkey, 2.15 km NE of Doġanşehir­Turkey, 3. Çimenlik­Ömerli­Turkey, 4. 20 km S of Cizre, 5. Erivan­Armenia, 6. Asi­Ararat­Turkey, 7. Megri (= Elisabethpol) ­ Armenia, 8. Ordubad­Azerbaijan, 9. Jarmo­Iraq, 10. Varamin­Iran, 11. S of Dezful (= Dizful) ­ Iran, 12. Masjhed Solaiman­Iran, 13. Around Shiras­Iran. R. arabicus — 1. Aden­Yemen. Sources: Jan 1862; Günther 1864; Hart 1891; Boulenger 1894; Anderson 1898; Nikolsy 1905; Werner 1906, 1917; Wettstein 1928; Flower 1933; Müller & Wettstein 1933; Tschernow 1935; Schmidt 1933, 1939; Werner 1939; Reed & Marx 1959; Haas & Werner 1969; Darevsky 1970; Eiselt 1970; Bannikov et al. 1977; Esterbauer 1985, 1992; Latifi 1991; Berger Dell’Mour 1986; Gasperetti 1988; Leviton et al. 1992; Baha El Din 1994; Franzen & Bischoff 1995]." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/175401/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

